We recommended that Management:
a. Conduct a physical inventory of all properties of the Municipality at year-end in support to the preparation of the RCPPE and RPCLRN;
b. Designate an Inventory Committee who will conduct physical inventory of all PPE items of the Municipality;
c. Instruct General Services Officer -designate to maintain a local road inventory and property cards per category of PPE;
d. Require the Inventory Committee and Accounting Department to prepare the RCPPE/RPCLRN and reconcile the results of the physical count with the accounting records;
e. Require the Inventory Committee to submit the RCPPE/RPCLRN and submit the same to the Audit Team within the prescribed period; and
f. Require the Municipal Accountant to ensure that the accounting and reporting procedures laid-out in COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 25, 2015 are strictly followed. Above partial and unimplemented recommendations were reiterated in Part II of this report.

Recommendations:
• Cease the grant of cash advances without legally specific purpose;
• Avoid granting additional cash advance unless the previous cash advance given is first settled or a proper accounting thereof is made;
• Stop the grant of cash advances to elected officials other than cash advances for traveling expenses;
• Grant cash advances only to officials designated as disbursing officers; and
• Initiate the filing of appropriate administrative proceedings for those who failed to render their accountabilities after demand or those who failed to liquidate their cash advances in full pursuant to Civil Service Memorandum Circular No. 12, s.2012.

2.6 To avoid accumulation of outstanding cash advances, we recommended and
management agreed to the following:
➢ Cease the grant of cash advances without legally specific purpose;
➢ Avoid granting additional cash advance unless the previous cash
advance given is first settled or a proper accounting thereof is made;
➢ Demand the immediate settlement/liquidation of the outstanding cash
advances of all concerned officials and employees and support it with
proper documents;
➢ Stop the grant of cash advances to elected officials other than cash
advances for traveling expenses;
➢ Grant cash advances only to officials designated as disbursing officers;
and
➢ Initiate the filing of appropriate administrative proceedings for those
who failed to render their accountabilities after demand or those who
failed to liquidate their cash advances in full pursuant to Civil Service
Memorandum Circular No. 12, s.2012.

We have recommended to management the following:
 During the preparation of its GAD Accomplishment Report, administer the HGDG test on its GAD PPAs which will serve as basis in determining the actual expenditure that can be attributed to the GAD budget pursuant to Item 4.1.4.5.e of JMC No. 2013-01;
 Administer the HGDG test on its PPAs for CY 2015 and onwards, the results of which shall be the basis in estimating the cost of gender mainstreaming and the GAD budget.
